TECHNICAL REGULATIONS OF THE RUSSIAN INDOOR CHAMPIONSHIP OF THE ARAF, ALL-RUSSIAN INDOOR COMPETITIONS
from 02/14/2021 20:40
15-17 February 2021,
CSKA LFK arena, Moscow, Leningradsky Prospekt, 39, building 1
Arrival day is February 14, 2021, departure day is February 18, 2021.
AGE OF PARTICIPANTS, TEAM AND INDIVIDUAL CLASSIFICATIONS, ADMISSION CONDITIONS
The competition is individual with a team standings, athletes from teams of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation participate in the same age group - men and women.
Athletes of younger age groups are allowed to participate in sports competitions among men and women (born in 1998) if they have the necessary sports qualifications.
Athletes admitted to competition only in the individual event do not participate in the distribution of points in the team event.
The results of athletes who did not take part in these competitions will not be re-calculated, and points will not be awarded for the team standings.
All teams whose athletes compete in accordance with the approved territorial affiliation are awarded team points in full.
Participating organizations are allowed to include two athletes in each relay event in addition to the quota.
In relay racing, team members are required to wear uniforms of the same color.
In case of violation of this point of the regulations, the team may not be admitted to the competition.
In relay racing, athletes can only compete for a team from one territory.
Athletes with a sports category of at least 1st are allowed to participate in the competition.
Athletes declared by regional teams who have passed a medical examination and received permission from a doctor are allowed to participate in the competition.
Applications for the competition are accepted only through the unified information system of the All-Russian Athletics Federation.
The deadline for submitting applications for the competition is February 12, 2021, 18:00 Moscow time.
The committee for admitting participants and confirming applications sent in advance and providing the necessary documents for the application will work on February 14 from 10:00 to 16:00 in the CSKA LFK arena, in the conference hall lobby, 3rd floor, at the address: Leningradsky Prospekt, 39, building 1.
All athletes, coaches and representatives included in the team application are required to complete educational anti-doping online courses on the official RUSADA website and receive a certificate before the start of the competition.
ATHLETES, COACHES, REPRESENTATIVES ARE REQUIRED TO PROVIDE THE SECRETARIAT WITH A CERTIFICATE WITH A NEGATIVE RESULT OF THE PPR TEST FOR SOUTH EDUCATIONAL SCIENCE-19, WITH THE DATE OF COLLECTION OF THE BIOMATERIAL NO LATER THAN 72 HOURS FROM THE TIME OF APPEARANCE AT THE CREDENTIALS COMMISSION.
The territorial affiliation of athletes is determined in accordance with the Unified Information System and the decision of the Transfer Commission.
Official training at the competition arena on February 14 from 16:00 to 19:00. On competition days - outside of competition time.
Pre-start warm-up is carried out on site, under the supervision of senior discipline judges.
The gathering and registration of participants will take place at the registration area (Sai Koot).
Sai Koot will be located behind the second turn next to the shot put sector.
When registering, the participant must show the judge the appropriately attached bib number.
The exit of participants from the registration area to the competition areas in technical events is carried out under the supervision of the senior judge/referee for the event, and in running events - under the supervision of the assistant starter.
Participants are prohibited from leaving the competition venue without the referee&#39;s permission.
Registration of participants in running events begins 40 minutes before the event and ends 10 minutes before the start of the event.
Registration for technical events begins 50 minutes and ends 25 minutes before the start of the event.
Registration for the pole vault starts 80 minutes and ends 55 minutes before the start of the event.
Participants who fail to register will not be allowed to participate in the competition.
Participants are given trial attempts in accordance with the Rules of the sport.
In the 60m race and 60m hurdles, the competition is held in 3 rounds, with entry into the next round determined after the application deadline.
In the 200 m, 400 m and 800 m races, the competitions are held in 2 laps, with the final determined by time.
In the event of a tie in the running events when advancing to the next round, the tie is resolved in the following manner: 1. Checking the results to an accuracy of 1/1000; 2. If after applying paragraph 1 the tie remains, then a draw is held.
Final races are held in the 1500 m, 3000 m, 5000 m and 4x400 m races.
In jumping and throwing, there are qualifying (in the case of more than 16 registered athletes) and final competitions, in order to participate in which it is necessary to pass the qualification.
If the number of participants who have met the standard is less than 12 people, then athletes reach this number in accordance with the best qualification results.
If a participant, declared in several types of the program, does not appear for one of the types without a valid reason, then he is not allowed to compete in subsequent types.
Athletes are allowed to use personal equipment, provided that such equipment is approved by the Organizing Committee.
The athlete must hand over personal equipment (shot) for inspection to the equipment service (inventory room in the warm-up area) no later than 2 hours before the start of the event.
During the competition it is not permitted to replace the equipment.
In case of a tie in determining the winner in vertical jumps, a jump-off is held.
All protests and appeals shall be made in accordance with the Rules - Rule 8 (146).
An oral protest is made by the representative/athlete immediately after the announcement of the result that gave rise to the protest.
A written appeal must be submitted no later than 30 minutes after the official announcement of the result for a given event.
Protests and appeals concerning the right of athletes to participate in competitions or their membership in a particular team are submitted in a similar manner to the Jury of Appeal.
The results of the team standings are determined in accordance with the Regulations. The results of all-Russian competitions, including those of the team standings, are accepted.
The winner and prize winners of the running events are required to appear in person at the awards department located in the arena no later than 10 minutes after the end of the event.
The winners of the championship are awarded with championship medals, the winners of the all-Russian competitions (200 m and 5000 m)
Any athlete who fails to start in a running or technical event is not allowed to participate in subsequent events and is considered to have withdrawn from the competition.
If an athlete advances to the next round after the preliminary round of the competition but then does not compete in that event, he or she will be disqualified from participating in further events, including the relay.
In the event that an athlete presents medical documents indicating that he is unable to participate in any type of competition, the technical delegate may decide to allow him to participate in other disciplines of the competition, but only on the following day.
During the competition, the doctor is located in the area provided by the organizers.
The technical meeting of the State Sports Committee with official representatives of the teams will take place on February 14 at 18:00 in the conference hall of the CSKA Sports and Fitness Club arena.
The meeting of the members of the State Jury with the competition panel of judges will take place on February 14 at 18:40 in the conference hall of the CSKA LFK arena.
