THE EXTRAORDINARY ADVENTURES OF ADELE
The most daring adventure film of the decade hints that The Extraordinary Adventures of Adele will begin like Amelie, veer towards Jurassic Park, continue with Indiana Jones and The Mummy, and end with Titanic.
The film is based on the first volume of Jacques Tardi&#39;s comics about journalist Adele Blanc-Sec.
Louise Bourgoin starred in only three films before Adele.
The actress became famous for her role in The Girl from Monaco, for which she was nominated for a Cesar Award.
The director does not run after the viewer with an outstretched hand, begging him to appreciate the special effects, scenery or tricks, but draws him along, like an old-fashioned novelist exclaiming before a great journey to the center of the earth or to the ends of the earth: “Forward, my reader, great things await us!”
At the same time, Besson treats genre cinema, about which he knows absolutely everything, unceremoniously and cheerfully, like a boy who has watched too many old films and read too much Jules Verne.
