COMING OUT JULY 22
“Adele...” is a case where a parody becomes the pinnacle of the genre itself and is capable of radically changing it, directing it along a new path.
This was the case with Sergio Leone&#39;s spaghetti westerns, Quentin Tarantino&#39;s gangster action films, the aforementioned &quot;Indiana Jones&quot; (he was both bowed to and ridiculed here), and finally, with the same &quot;Fifth Element&quot;.
Besson&#39;s style in this film is made up of verbal trickery, acting clowning and plot balancing (circus terms are quite appropriate - the unity of the two arts here is organic and strong as never before).
A few words should be said about Adele herself.
She embodied the undeservedly forgotten type of adventurer who takes not so much by exploiting sexuality, but by pure courage and bravery.
In the movies, such girls are usually assigned some kind of macho or doe-eyed romantic guy on duty.
