The critics again grimaced, but the public again liked it - Liebesman worked in the spirit of the &quot;new horrors&quot;, which emphasize the excessive physiological nature of violence.
In general, his example shows how an entire genre is convulsing, trying to invent new ways of influencing a jaded public: the naturalistic bloodshed of splatters merges with the catch-up of slashers.
