Somnologist names causes of sleep problems
Sleep doctor Sofia Cherkasova spoke about foods and habits that interfere with healthy sleep.
As the specialist noted, sleep problems often arise due to products containing caffeine.
We are talking primarily about tea, coffee, chocolate and any desserts containing cocoa.
Their use before bedtime should be limited, since they not only interfere with falling asleep, but also make sleep “ragged”, which means it does not allow the body to fully recover.
According to the doctor, it is better to stop consuming caffeine-containing products 6-8 hours before bedtime.
Otherwise, they contribute to a decrease in the excitability threshold of the nervous system and, as a result, difficulties with falling asleep arise.
Alcohol also negatively affects the ability to fall asleep.
The doctor clarifies that small doses of alcoholic beverages promote relaxation and do not affect sleep.
However, amounts exceeding 36 grams in terms of pure alcohol lead to various sleep disorders, such as shallow sleep and frequent night awakenings.
In addition, to prevent problems with falling asleep, a somnologist recommends avoiding spicy foods in large portions.
Large volumes and spicy foods contribute to an increase in internal body temperature, which negatively affects the ability to fall asleep.
For healthy sleep it is necessary not only to maintain the external temperature regime - the optimal air temperature is 18-20 degrees - but also the absence of elevated body temperature.
According to Cherkasova, one should not overindulge in heavy food before bed, as it will not allow the body to fully recover and rest: it will be forced to spend energy on digestion.
The doctor also reminded that the lack of healthy sleep and accumulated sleep deprivation affect the quality of life and usual activities, so it is extremely important to adhere to a sleep and rest regimen and allow the body to recover.
