Management company from Kirov has had its license revoked
The Arbitration Court of the Kirov Region has revoked the license for entrepreneurial activity in the management of apartment buildings issued to the management company &quot;Zabota&quot;.
In the Kirov region, by decision of the regional Arbitration Court, the license for entrepreneurial activity in the management of apartment buildings previously issued to the management company &quot;Zabota&quot; was revoked.
According to the regional State Housing Inspectorate, the court decision was made back in November 2022, but it only came into force in February 2023.
The arbitration court revoked the management company&#39;s license because the organization ignored the State Housing Inspectorate&#39;s orders several times.
Currently, all objects that were under the management of &quot;Care&quot; have been excluded from the register of licenses for the implementation of entrepreneurial activity in the management of apartment buildings.
Their total area was 64.8 thousand square meters.
All houses are located in the regional center.
The Kirov administration knows that they are left without a management company.
In accordance with the requirements of Russian legislation, the State Housing Inspectorate informed the mayor&#39;s office about the current situation.
Let us recall that in January 2023, the Governor of the Kirov Region, Alexander Sokolov, set the task for the employees of the State Housing Inspectorate to liquidate 2/3 of the region&#39;s management companies by spring, since there are too many of them.
The legality of the governor&#39;s demands raised doubts among the Kirov communists.
They contacted the regional prosecutor&#39;s office and asked that Sokolov be held administratively liable.
Presumably, the Federal Antimonopoly Service could have taken the same position.
Anti-monopoly authorities also allegedly asked the prosecutor&#39;s office to check the legality of the regional leader&#39;s actions.
Wildberries will make bags at pick-up points paid
The Wildberries marketplace will make packages at order pick-up points paid from February 13.
Their cost will vary from 6 to 15 rubles.
Currently, packages are provided by the owners of pick-up points.
In case of their absence, a fine is imposed.
From Monday, February 13, packages can no longer be taken for free from Wildberries pick-up points.
Marketplace users received a notification stating that buyers who need the package will have to pay between 6 and 15 rubles for it.
This amount will be debited from the card specified in your personal account.
As the company indicated, this step will help reduce the use of plastic and will contribute to the preservation of nature.
As follows from the appendix to the offer for the provision of services for the delivery of parcels to individuals, the contractor, that is, the person who opened the pick-up point, must provide packages free of charge at the request of the client.
Moreover, they must be designed in certain colors and have a specified image.
Packages are purchased at the expense of the owners of the pick-up points; if this obligation is not fulfilled, they are subject to a fine of 10,000 rubles for each violation.
Previously, Wildberries clients caught the platform writing off funds from cards whose data had previously been deleted from their personal accounts.
This comes with major security risks, buyers fear.
The support service, in turn, explained that this is provided for in the user agreement.
As follows from it, the company has the right to write off money from deleted cards without notifying the client if payment from others does not go through for one reason or another.
Commenting on the situation, the company stated that settlements with customers are carried out with the permission of the clients, and no leakage of bank card data can occur.
